<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The macro LFS_LOCK(cfg) is defined as ((void)cfg,0) which always evaluates to 0. Thus the assignment 'int err = LFS_LOCK(lfs->cfg);' sets err to a constant 0 and the subsequent controlling expression 'if (err)' is invariant (always false). This violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 14.3 (controlling expressions shall not be invariant).
</scenario>
